business, a relatively obscure but powerful competitor that
operates extensively in the former Soviet Union has been increasing
its control in a region responsible for much of the world's supply.
Trans-World Group, already the largest seller of aluminum ingots,
has been concentrating its effort in Ukraine, forming an alliance
with the government that could hurt its few remaining regional
competitors. By Tom Warner. (With map).
