<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Four at WestPoint dispose of shares
 &HT;    By Robert Luke
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Four insiders at home furnishings maker WestPoint Stevens last
month sold a total 68,011 Class A shares, raising more than $2.1
million.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, two insiders at Carmike Cinemas, whose shares are
trading at about half of what they were selling for a year earlier,
boosted their stakes.
</P>
<P>
   At WestPoint Stevens, William F. Crumley, executive vice
president of manufacturing, sold 9,519 shares July 27 at between
$30.50 and $30.63 each, totaling $291,414. He now holds 107,960
shares directly and indirectly, worth $2,881,183 at Friday's price
of $26.68 3/4 on Nasdaq.
</P>
<P>
   Charles W. McCall, director, exercised an option for 20,000
shares July 23-27 at $9.50 each, totaling $190,000. The former
chairman of McKesson HBOC then sold 22,500 shares at $32.50 each,
totaling $731,250. He now holds 113,762 shares directly and
indirectly, worth $3,036,023.
</P>
<P>
   Morgan M. Schuessler, chief financial officer, sold 28,000
shares July 26-27 at between $30.66 and $30.71 each, totaling
$859,130. He now holds 186,646 shares directly and indirectly,
worth $4,981,115.
</P>
<P>
   Dale C. Williams, executive vice president of international
sales and marketing, sold 7,992 shares July 27 at between $30.63
and $30.69 each, totaling $245,005. Williams now holds 43,987
shares, worth $1,173,903.
</P>
<P>
   At Carmike Cinemas, John W. Jordan II, director, indirectly
bought 57,200 Class A shares July 2-8 at $15.50 each, totaling
$886,600. He now holds 448,205 shares indirectly, worth $6,078,780
at Friday's price of $13.56 1/4 on the New York Stock Exchange.
David W. Zalaznick, director, bought 50,000 Class A shares July
22-23 at between $13.44 and $13.50 each, totaling $673,942. He now
holds 276,790 shares, worth $3,753,964.
</P>
<P>
   The Securities and Exchange Commission requires insiders
(officers, directors, persons with policy-making roles) to report
their transactions within 10 days after the month in which they
took place. Beneficial owners, or those owning 10 percent or more
of any publicly held company, also must report.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
