   This week, for a sold-out five-show run at the FleetCenter that
kicked off in raucous style Saturday night, it's Bruce
Springsteen's turn.
</P>
<P>
   The Boss is back, reunited with his E Street Band mates. To rock
mavens, it feels a little like a visit from the pope, or a playoff
series against the Yankees. Horowitz, backed by the New York
Philharmonic. Olivier, with the Royal Shakespeare Company, on tour
as Lear.
</P>
<P>
   Springsteen did not disappoint the faithful. He opened the show
with ``The Ties that Bind,'' as good a description as any of his
