<HEADER>
A5702 &Cx1f; tth-z
u l BC-FASHION-POCKETS-ART-S     08-22 0423
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASHION-POCKETS-ART-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MULTIPLE POCKETS ARE BECOMING MAINSTREAM 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By SUSAN PHINNEY  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Think of pockets as a new accessory, something to compete with
jewelry, handbags or other holdalls.
</P>
<P>
   Multiple pockets _ once found only in frumpy travel clothes and
pocket-covered vests favored by photographers or fly-fishing fans _
are becoming mainstream.
</P>
<P>
   But not all these new pockets are so obvious. A pair of plain
khaki pants has midthigh pockets accessed by a zipper hidden in the
inseam. A windbreaker has an extra pocket on a sleeve.
</P>
<P>
   Pockets are also sewn onto belts sold with sleek pants. It keeps
the pants line bulge-free and gives the occupant a place to stow
essentials.
</P>
<P>
   Even a strapless evening gown from Yves Saint Laurent, shown in
a recent Nordstrom show, has pockets hidden in some delicate
shirring around hips and waist. A woman who pays $1,630 for this
dress won't have to buy an evening bag to go with it.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps people are simply tired of lugging around bags or being
weighted down with fanny or back packs. Perhaps it's a backlash
against minimalist fashion.
</P>
<P>
   But once they discovered the multipocketed convenience and
comfort of cargo pants, there was no chance for pocketless garments
and those with plain old pockets.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Julian, New York-based trend-watcher, says this pocket surge
is ``all about utilitarian fashion ... mobile dressing ... clothes
that adapt to us.'' He says it's taking cargo pants to the next
level.
</P>
<P>
   Sean wood, assistant manager at Seattle's Zebra Club, says
multipocket fashions are part of the high-tech and military
influences driving segments of the fashion business.
</P>
<P>
   At Zebra Club, there's a women's camisole ($40) complete with
two zippered pockets plus a cell-phone pocket all on one skimpy
little top. A hooded sweat shirt ($88) has a zippered patch pocket
set at an angle across the front.
</P>
<P>
   Even a plain, ribbed turtleneck women's sweater ($88) has a big
patch pocket just below the collar.
</P>
<P>
   The Powder Room has a classic pink buttoned-down shirt ($34.95).
But turn it around and there's a huge pocket across the back. Even
a short black cocktail dress ($36.95) has an oversize patch pocket
on one hip.
</P>
<P>
   Old Navy stores are another source of high-pocket clothes.
Here's where to find six-pocket carpenter pants ($30), utility
vests with five pockets ($34), or sweatshirt-like sweaters with
hoods, front zippers and two big front pockets ($29.50).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-22-99 1820EDT &QL; 
