   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-DRASKOVIC (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ Vuk Draskovic, the
charismatic leader of the Serbian Renewal Movement, and his
influential wife, Danica, find themselves at a political
crossroads, suddenly less radical than many of their supporters,
their commitment to the ouster of Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic called into question. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-CASTELLI (New York) _ Leo Castelli, the New York art dealer
who played an extraordinary role in shaping contemporary American
art and fostering international acceptance of painters like Jasper
Johns, Robert Rauschenberg, Roy Lichtenstein and Frank Stella, died
on Saturday night at his Manhattan home. He was 91. By John
Russell. (With a photo.)
