<P>
   ORGANIC-FARMS (CALHOUN, Mo.) _ Gary Anson worries that today's
chicken manure isn't what it used to be. He struggles mightily to
keep his corn, soybeans and wheat pristine _ free of chemicals and
laboratory-tinkered genetics. When he succeeds, his crops earn
organic status and fetch a premium price. But keeping his fields
unspoiled by high-tech agriculture is a chore without end. By SCOTT
