<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Monday, Aug.
23, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   GATES-CHARITY (Seattle) _ The world's wealthiest man has created
America's wealthiest charity. Bill and Melinda Gates have
consolidated the William H. Gates Foundation and the Gates Learning
Foundation into the $17.1 billion Bill and Melinda Gates
Foundation. The Gateses have boosted the foundation by $15.1
billion this year alone, including $6 billion this month.
</P>
<P>
   By Neil Modie. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   DISASTERS-GOVERNMENT (Undated) _ Congress insists that citizens
have a right to know the dangers they face from nearby factories or
chemical plants, but the CIA, FBI and other security agencies want
to keep secret exactly how bad things can get if there are
catastrophic leaks or explosions. To show the government means
business, on Aug. 5 President Clinton signed an order which
authorized criminal sentences and fines of $1 million a day against
anyone who releases parts of that information to an unauthorized
person.
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Schneider. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-LABOR (Seattle) _ The Boeing Co. and the International
Association of Machinists face the first real threat to their
negotiations as they battle over the company's practice of ignoring
seniority to tap workers for special promotions.
</P>
